THAN SANTA.

12:05.192 --> 12:06.891
BUT I'LL TELL YOU
A SECRET.

12:06.893 --> 12:08.093
YOU READY?

12:08.095 --> 12:10.929
DADS AND SONS
ARE THE SAME.

12:10.931 --> 12:14.799
MADE FROM THE SAME PARTS
AND THE SAME PIECES.

12:14.801 --> 12:19.104
SO THAT MEANS YOU HAVE YOUR
DAD'S COURAGE RIGHT IN THERE.

12:19.106 --> 12:21.206
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW IT
'CAUSE YOU HAVEN'T TRIED IT OUT

12:21.208 --> 12:22.907
ON SOMETHING
YOU'RE SUPER SCARED OF,

12:22.909 --> 12:23.942
BUT YOU HAVE IT.

12:23.944 --> 12:25.276
I PROMISE.

12:25.278 --> 12:28.213
FEEL IT?
IS IT IN THERE?

12:28.215 --> 12:29.481
YEAH?

12:29.483 --> 12:31.015
GO GET 'EM.

12:31.017 --> 12:32.917
Girl: CHEESE!

12:32.919 --> 12:35.920
YOU READY
TO GO SEE SANTA?

12:35.922 --> 12:36.921
[ WOMAN LAUGHS ]

12:36.923 --> 12:38.890
THANKS, SANTA!

12:38.892 --> 12:41.993
I WANT TO SEE
THE PICTURE, MOM!

12:41.995 --> 12:44.763
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

12:44.765 --> 12:47.365
I GOT THE SNOWBALL
AND CANDY-CANE ONES.

12:47.367 --> 12:48.466
THAT'S GREAT.

12:51.204 --> 12:54.272
LET'S GO HOME
AND PUT THEM UP.

12:55.442 --> 12:57.041
¶ IT'S CHRISTMASTIME ¶

12:57.043 --> 12:58.910
Ben: NAT,
MOM'LL BE HOME SOON,

12:58.912 --> 13:01.045
SO IF YOU WANT TO CHANGE BEFORE
THE FAIR, YOU PROBABLY --

13:01.047 --> 13:02.547
OKAY,
I FOUND ONE.

13:02.549 --> 13:04.249
THIS IS
SO HURTING ME.

13:04.251 --> 13:05.416
HERE.
GRAB THAT.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.118
I DIDN'T EVEN
PUT IT IN YET.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.920
OKAY.
HERE? IS THAT GOOD?

13:08.922 --> 13:10.221
NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

13:10.223 --> 13:11.456
FURTHER.
OH, MAN.

13:11.458 --> 13:12.791
HERE?

13:12.793 --> 13:14.192
YEAH. FURTHER.
FURTHER.

13:14.194 --> 13:15.193
KEEP IT COMING.

13:15.195 --> 13:16.427
COME ON.
HE'S GONNA FALL.

13:16.429 --> 13:17.562
FURTHER THAN THAT?
YEP.

13:17.564 --> 13:18.997
IT NEEDS
TO BE FURTHER.

13:18.999 --> 13:20.365
IT'S RIGHT OVER
THE THING THERE.

13:20.367 --> 13:21.800
COME ON.
KEEP IT COMING.

13:21.802 --> 13:23.001
OH, MY GOD.
[ GROANS ]

13:23.003 --> 13:25.003
OH, GOD!

13:25.005 --> 13:27.138
[ LAUGHS ]

13:27.140 --> 13:28.907
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:28.909 --> 13:30.542
I'M GOING TO KILL YOU.

13:30.544 --> 13:32.110
[ LAUGHING ]

13:32.112 --> 13:33.878
OOH!
OH!

13:33.880 --> 13:35.413
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:35.415 --> 13:38.049
GET DOWN!

13:38.051 --> 13:39.184
[ LAUGHS ]

13:39.186 --> 13:41.953
CAN I GET A LADDER,
PLEASE?

13:41.955 --> 13:43.388
[ SIGHS ] YES.

13:43.390 --> 13:45.156
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:45.158 --> 13:46.524
[ LAUGHING ]

13:46.526 --> 13:48.226
ABBY, DON'T -- DON'T GROW UP
TO BE LIKE THIS ONE.

13:48.228 --> 13:51.296
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

14:39.479 --> 14:41.512
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

14:41.514 --> 14:42.981
Christy: BEN?

14:45.385 --> 14:46.985
YOU READY?
WE HAVE TO GO.

14:46.987 --> 14:49.520
UH, JUST GIVE ME
TWO MINUTES.

15:29.396 --> 15:32.563
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

15:40.073 --> 15:43.041
[ SIGHS ]

15:43.043 --> 15:44.208
HERE YOU GO.

15:44.210 --> 15:46.077
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

15:49.349 --> 15:50.648
MOM,
I'M GONNA GO.

15:50.650 --> 15:53.251
WHY DON'T WE STAY TOGETHER
FOR A LITTLE BIT?

15:53.253 --> 15:54.619
MOM?

15:54.621 --> 15:56.587
GO ON.
[ SCOFFS ]

15:56.589 --> 16:00.258
STILL GIVING YOU
THE SILENT TREATMENT?

16:00.260 --> 16:01.592
SHE'S GOING
FOR THE RECORD.

16:01.594 --> 16:03.361
YEAH, WELL,
SHE HAS TO ACCEPT THE FACT

16:03.363 --> 16:05.363
THAT HER PARENTS
ARE PEOPLE WHO MAKE MISTAKES,

16:05.365 --> 16:06.597
JUST LIKE
EVERYONE ELSE.

16:06.599 --> 16:08.333
YEAH, RIGHT.

16:08.334 --> 16:10.068
DADDY,
CAN I GET SOME COTTON CANDY?

16:10.070 --> 16:12.070
YEAH. SURE.

16:12.072 --> 16:13.538
HERE.

16:14.741 --> 16:16.708
MM.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.978
YOU SEE IT?

16:19.980 --> 16:21.346
COME ON.

16:21.348 --> 16:22.814
IT'S HAPPENING.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.281
YEAH, WELL,
WE'RE NOT GONNA HIDE.

16:24.284 --> 16:25.750
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

16:29.022 --> 16:29.988
UH...
OH...

16:29.990 --> 16:31.255
AAH!
YOU OKAY?

16:31.257 --> 16:32.256
<i> I WANT CIDER.</i>

16:32.258 --> 16:33.725
DO YOU SEE LISA?
LISA!

16:33.727 --> 16:35.994
HE'S RIGHT HERE.

16:35.996 --> 16:38.062
OH!
IT'S OKAY.

16:38.064 --> 16:40.431
I CAN'T TAKE MY EYES OFF HIM
FOR ONE SECOND.

16:40.433 --> 16:43.701
<i> BLUE WALL CIDER.</i>

16:43.703 --> 16:45.386
OH, OF COURSE.
OF COURSE.

16:45.387 --> 16:47.070
THE CIDER STAND'S
USUALLY BY THE BLUE WALL.

16:47.073 --> 16:48.706
OHH.
WELL,
THAT'S WHY HE GOT LOST.

16:48.708 --> 16:51.376
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TAKE ME
FOR CIDER, MATTY?

16:51.378 --> 16:53.778
YEAH, WHY DON'T YOU DO THAT,
MATTY?

16:53.780 --> 16:56.080
LET'S GO.
THERE YOU GO.

16:56.082 --> 16:56.748
I'LL BE BACK.

16:56.750 --> 16:58.416
OH, THANK YOU.
HEY.

16:58.418 --> 17:00.752
MAN, THAT KID
LIKES HIS CIDER, HUH?

17:00.754 --> 17:02.720
THE SINGLES SCENE
IS DEAD.

17:02.722 --> 17:04.756
OH, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT.

17:04.758 --> 17:06.691
OOH.
I SPOKE TOO SOON.

17:06.693 --> 17:10.661
THERE'S A HOTTIE WITH A BODY
AT YOUR 10.

17:10.663 --> 17:12.597
OH,
I KNOW HER.

17:12.599 --> 17:15.033
YOU KNOW HER?!

17:15.035 --> 17:17.168
YEAH,
HER NAME'S ALLISON.

17:17.170 --> 17:20.104
SHE'S IN NATALIE'S CLASS.
SHE'S 16.

17:20.106 --> 17:21.539
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

17:21.541 --> 17:23.174
I'M GOING TO HELL.

17:23.176 --> 17:25.376
Christy:
THE RICHARDSONS ARE HERE.

17:25.378 --> 17:26.778
I'M GONNA GET
A SNACK.

17:26.780 --> 17:28.046
LET'S GO SAY HI.

17:29.749 --> 17:31.282
[ BEN SIGHS ]

17:31.284 --> 17:33.751
IGNORE HIM.

17:33.753 --> 17:36.621
HEY, BEN, WHY DON'T YOU COME
AND JOIN US OVER HERE?

17:36.623 --> 17:39.724
HEY, JOE.
GOOD TO SEE YOU OUT.

17:39.726 --> 17:43.227
NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
CHRISTY.

17:43.229 --> 17:45.163
WE WERE
JUST LEAVING.

17:45.165 --> 17:46.798
GOING SO SOON,
KEV?

17:46.800 --> 17:48.767
[ SIGHS ]

17:48.768 --> 17:50.735
CHRISTY, BEN,
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU BOTH.

17:50.737 --> 17:52.637
HAPPY HOLIDAYS.
YOU, TOO.

17:52.639 --> 17:53.638
HAPPY HOLIDAYS.

17:53.640 --> 17:55.190
BYE.

17:55.191 --> 17:56.741
Vanessa: I WOULDN'T
TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

17:56.743 --> 17:59.277
THAT MAN'S JUST
NATURALLY ANTI-SOCIAL.

17:59.279 --> 18:00.511
I SUPPOSE.

18:00.513 --> 18:02.113
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M USED TO IT.

18:02.115 --> 18:03.431
Craig: OW!

18:03.432 --> 18:04.748
Abby: THAT'S NOT TRUE!
TAKE IT BACK!

18:04.751 --> 18:06.150
OW! YOU HURT ME!
YOU'RE A LIAR!

18:06.152 --> 18:07.418
TAKE IT BACK!
DID NOT!

18:07.420 --> 18:08.486
TAKE IT BACK!

18:08.488 --> 18:09.854
Abby: THAT'S NOT TRUE!
ABBY!

18:09.856 --> 18:11.339
IT'S NOT MY FAULT.
WHAT HAPPENED?

18:11.340 --> 18:12.823
CRAIG'S A LIAR.
WE -- WE WERE JUST
KIDDING AROUND,

18:12.826 --> 18:14.826
AND THEN SHE WENT ALL CRAZY
AND PUSHED ME.

18:14.828 --> 18:17.428
YOU CAN'T JUST GO AROUND
HITTING PEOPLE, YOUNG LADY.

18:17.430 --> 18:18.780
THANKS, MAN.

18:18.781 --> 18:20.131
I'LL -- I'LL DEAL
WITH MY DAUGHTER.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.100
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU PUSH HIM?

18:22.102 --> 18:23.868
HE CALLED YOU
A "BABY KILLER."

18:25.672 --> 18:27.756
THAT'S NOT OKAY.

18:27.757 --> 18:29.841
CRAIG, YOU APOLOGIZE TO ABBY
RIGHT NOW.

18:29.843 --> 18:32.743
BUT YOU SAID IT --
<i> NOW.</i>

18:32.745 --> 18:35.880
I'M SORRY.

18:37.517 --> 18:39.317
ABBY.

18:40.787 --> 18:43.654
DAD...

18:45.658 --> 18:48.192
I'M SORRY.

18:49.696 --> 18:52.196
YOU SHOULDN'T SAY THINGS
LIKE THAT.

18:52.198 --> 18:54.465
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE HE HEARD IT.

18:56.669 --> 18:59.237
GO.

18:59.239 --> 19:02.140
[ SIGHS ]

19:08.515 --> 19:11.415
LET'S GO.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.851
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

19:28.434 --> 19:30.868
[ PANTING ]

19:42.882 --> 19:46.517
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

19:49.556 --> 19:52.623
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

20:00.366 --> 20:03.868
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

20:05.438 --> 20:07.505
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

20:08.508 --> 20:10.875
I KNOW EXACTLY...

20:22.922 --> 20:24.822
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:24.824 --> 20:27.358
UM, DETECTIVE CORNELL
WANTS A RECEIPT

20:27.360 --> 20:29.460
FROM THE FLASHLIGHT
I BOUGHT YOU,

20:29.462 --> 20:31.762
BUT THE FILES ARE IN THE CABINET
AND IT'S LOCKED.

20:31.764 --> 20:34.265
ISN'T SCOTT MURPHY
IN CUSTODY?

20:34.267 --> 20:37.268
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY TO SHARE THE
DETAILS OF THE CASE WITH YOU.

20:37.270 --> 20:41.239
BEN, SHE SAID THE RECEIPT COULD
HELP ELIMINATE YOU AS A SUSPECT.

20:41.241 --> 20:43.441
IF THE MODEL OF YOUR FLASHLIGHT
IS DIFFERENT

20:43.443 --> 20:45.876
THAN THE ONE FORENSICS INDICATES
WAS THE MURDER WEAPON,

20:45.878 --> 20:47.478
THEN YOU'RE
OFF THE HOOK.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.914
DON'T YOU NEED
A SEARCH WARRANT?

20:49.916 --> 20:52.450
ONLY IF YOU'RE UNWILLING
TO COOPERATE.

20:52.452 --> 20:54.118
THE PROBLEM IS,

20:54.119 --> 20:55.785
IF I COME BACK HERE WITH A
WARRANT AND CSIs AND DETECTIVES,

20:55.788 --> 20:58.689
THE PRESS IS JUST GONNA FILM
THE WHOLE THING.

20:58.691 --> 21:00.424
AND NO MATTER
HOW I TRY TO PROTECT YOU,

21:00.426 --> 21:01.926
THEY'RE NOT
GONNA LISTEN.

21:01.928 --> 21:03.928
THOSE HYENAS
WILL JUST KEEP ROLLING

21:03.930 --> 21:05.830
AND LET THE PICTURE
TELL THE STORY.

21:05.832 --> 21:08.833
WE APPRECIATE YOU TAKING
ALL THAT INTO CONSIDERATION.

21:08.835 --> 21:11.269
BEN, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THE KEY IS?

21:11.271 --> 21:13.838
YEAH.
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

21:21.581 --> 21:23.648
[ SIGHS ]

21:29.289 --> 21:32.290
HERE WE GO.

21:40.366 --> 21:43.634
YOU OKAY,
MR. CRAWFORD?

21:45.772 --> 21:47.004
YOU'RE SWEATING.

21:47.006 --> 21:49.840
YEAH, I JUST
CAME BACK FROM A RUN.

21:50.810 --> 21:54.945
IT'S NICE YOU CAN KEEP UP
WITH YOUR ROUTINE.

21:54.947 --> 21:56.647
MOST PEOPLE WOULDN'T.

21:57.817 --> 21:59.950
Christy: I KNOW
IT'S IN HERE SOMEWHERE.

21:59.952 --> 22:02.386
WELL, I DON'T WANT TO TAKE UP
TOO MUCH OF YOUR TIME.

22:02.388 --> 22:04.021
I CAN DO THAT FOR YOU
IF IT'S EASIER.

22:08.428 --> 22:10.895
THANK YOU.

22:26.379 --> 22:28.846
Christy: NO, I HAVE NO CLUE
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

22:28.848 --> 22:30.715
PLEASE.
EVERY TIME I TURN MY BACK,

22:30.717 --> 22:32.883
YOU'RE HELPING THAT WOMAN
TRY TO PUT ME AWAY.

22:32.885 --> 22:33.984
HAVE YOU
LOST YOUR MIND?

22:33.986 --> 22:36.354
SHE THINKS I KILLED TOM!
YOU UNDERSTAND?!

22:36.356 --> 22:38.556
BUT YOU DIDN'T.
YOU'RE INNOCENT.

22:38.558 --> 22:41.625
THE MORE WE COOPERATE,
THE SOONER SHE'S GONNA SEE THAT.

22:41.627 --> 22:43.127
[ SIGHS ]
THAT'S SO NAIVE.

22:43.129 --> 22:45.830
THERE ARE COUNTLESS STORIES
OF INNOCENT MEN

22:45.832 --> 22:48.366
BEING EXONERATED
DECADES AFTER BEING IN PRISON,

22:48.368 --> 22:49.667
SOMETIMES AFTER
THEY WERE EXECUTED!

22:49.669 --> 22:51.802
SHE IS
A HOMICIDE DETECTIVE.

22:51.804 --> 22:54.672
SHE'S LOOKING AT EVERY POSSIBLE
ANGLE TO SOLVE TOM'S MURDER.

22:54.674 --> 22:56.607
HE WAS YOUR SON.

22:56.608 --> 22:58.541
I WOULD THINK YOU WOULD FEEL
SOME RESPONSIBILITY TO HELP HER.

23:00.913 --> 23:03.114
THAT WASN'T FAIR.

23:04.817 --> 23:07.618
WHAT IS?

23:07.620 --> 23:08.886
[ SIGHS ]

23:11.124 --> 23:15.693
CHRISTY,
I'VE SCREWED UP...

23:15.695 --> 23:18.329
A LOT.

23:18.330 --> 23:20.964
BUT I NEED YOU
TO STAND BY ME ON THIS,

23:20.967 --> 23:22.733
AND IF
YOU WON'T DO IT FOR ME,

23:22.735 --> 23:24.769
THEN CAN YOU PLEASE DO IT
FOR OUR GIRLS?

23:27.573 --> 23:29.907
YES,
OF COURSE.

23:29.909 --> 23:32.910
I AM.
AND I WILL.

23:35.448 --> 23:39.583
I'M LATE.
I HAVE TO GO.

23:41.821 --> 23:45.122
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:26.165 --> 24:29.066
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

24:31.070 --> 24:32.470
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

24:32.472 --> 24:34.155
BEN CRAWFORD.

24:34.156 --> 24:35.839
FENTON: Mr. Crawford,
I've got a job for you.

24:35.842 --> 24:36.941
REALLY?
Yeah.

24:36.943 --> 24:39.043
You available
in the near future?

24:39.045 --> 24:42.013
YES,
I'M AVAILABLE.

24:42.014 --> 24:44.982
I'LL TRY NOT TO GET UNDERFOOT,
BUT I WORK AT HOME, SO I'M HERE.

24:44.984 --> 24:46.617
Ben: WHAT KIND OF WORK
DO YOU DO?

24:46.619 --> 24:49.387
I'M A RESEARCHER.

24:49.388 --> 24:52.156
I USED TO BE ON STAFF AT ONE
OF THOSE BIG, ESTABLISHED FIRMS,

24:52.158 --> 24:54.525
BUT THAT WENT AWAY,
SO...

24:54.527 --> 24:56.894
NOW JOB TO JOB.

24:56.896 --> 24:58.128
I KNOW
HOW THAT IS.

24:58.130 --> 24:59.630
YEAH.

24:59.631 --> 25:01.131
AND, MAN, IT MUST BE TOUGH
GETTING WORK

25:01.133 --> 25:03.734
WITH YOUR FACE
ALL OVER THE NEWS.

25:03.736 --> 25:09.006
YEAH, I'M, UH, I'M REAL GRATEFUL
YOU WEREN'T SCARED OFF, SO...

25:09.008 --> 25:10.508
BELIEVE ME,
I GET IT.

25:10.510 --> 25:13.010
YOU KNOW,
WHEN WE WERE GETTING DIVORCED,

25:13.012 --> 25:14.879
MY EX --
SHE SUDDENLY REMEMBERED

25:14.881 --> 25:16.914
THAT I
SEXUALLY ASSAULTED HER.

25:16.916 --> 25:19.467
MM.
YEAH.

25:19.468 --> 25:22.019
ONE OF THOSE NIGHTMARE
CUSTODY FIGHTS YOU HEAR ABOUT.

25:22.021 --> 25:24.688
I'M SORRY.

25:24.690 --> 25:26.857
YEAH.

25:26.858 --> 25:29.025
I FOUND OUT RIGHT THEN HOW FAST
PEOPLE RUSH TO JUDGMENT.

25:29.028 --> 25:34.798
IT'S LIKE I WOKE UP ONE DAY
AND SUDDENLY, I WAS THE BAD GUY.

25:34.800 --> 25:36.066
YOU KNOW?

25:39.839 --> 25:41.939
IT'S PRETTY SURREAL.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.874
YEAH.

25:43.875 --> 25:45.808
BAD AS IT IS FOR ME,
I CAN'T IMAGINE

25:45.811 --> 25:47.177
HOW TERRIBLE
IT WAS FOR YOU

25:47.179 --> 25:50.147
TO FIND THAT LITTLE BOY
OUT THERE.

25:50.149 --> 25:52.283
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN AWFUL
FOR YOU.

25:52.285 --> 25:53.817
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

25:59.959 --> 26:01.759
OH,
I'M SORRY.

26:01.761 --> 26:03.294
I-I WASN'T THINKING.

26:03.296 --> 26:04.795
HEY,
LET ME HELP YOU DOWN.

26:04.797 --> 26:05.930
I'M ALL RIGHT,
MAN.

26:08.334 --> 26:11.869
Y-YOU HEAR SO MUCH
ABOUT A S-STORY IN THE NEWS,

26:11.871 --> 26:13.837
AND YOU FORGET
THAT REAL PEOPLE ARE INVOLVED.

26:13.839 --> 26:17.207
I JUST HAVE TO GO
PICK UP MY DAUGHTER.

26:17.209 --> 26:19.176
RIGHT.
OF COURSE.

26:19.178 --> 26:22.313
A-AND I'M SORRY...
AGAIN.

26:22.315 --> 26:27.084
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

26:28.854 --> 26:31.355
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

26:42.368 --> 26:46.704
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

27:04.857 --> 27:09.627
I BOUGHT THIS FOR YOU.

27:11.063 --> 27:15.065
IT'S JUST LIKE THE ONE I HAD
WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE.

27:15.067 --> 27:17.868
BACK WHEN
I GOT MY FIRST BIKE...

27:17.870 --> 27:20.871
YOU WOULDN'T TAKE IT OUT OF
THE GARAGE WITHOUT ONE OF THESE.

27:20.873 --> 27:23.290
[ BELL RINGS ]

27:23.291 --> 27:25.708
I WAS SAVING IT TO GIVE TO YOU
FOR CHRISTMAS

27:25.711 --> 27:30.347
TO GO WITH THE BIG-BOY BIKE
YOUR MOM WAS GONNA GET YOU.

27:30.349 --> 27:34.885
IT WAS JUST SITTING THERE
IN MY TRUCK.

27:34.887 --> 27:37.354
FORGOT I EVEN HAD IT.

27:38.357 --> 27:42.059
MERRY CHRISTMAS,
LITTLE MAN.

27:46.298 --> 27:48.198
Scott:
I HEAR YOU SAY THAT,

27:48.200 --> 27:51.001
AND I ASK MYSELF,
"IS THAT GRIEF? OR GUILT?"

27:51.003 --> 27:53.070
THEY LET YOU OUT?

27:53.072 --> 27:55.105
I HAD AN ALIBI.

27:55.107 --> 27:56.907
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

27:56.909 --> 28:00.911
WELL, THEN WHY DIDN'T YOU
COME FORWARD?

28:00.913 --> 28:02.913
MY ALIBI
WAS NICOLE,

28:02.915 --> 28:05.849
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO HURT JESS.

28:05.851 --> 28:07.885
OR YOU DIDN'T WANT THE MPs
TO FIND YOU.

28:07.887 --> 28:09.019
[ SCOFFS ]

28:09.021 --> 28:12.456
SO BRAVE
WHEN THEY'RE WATCHING.

28:12.458 --> 28:15.426
PEOPLE LIKE YOU, BUDDY,
HAVE NO IDEA.

28:15.428 --> 28:20.431
IN WORLD WAR II, GUYS SAW
40 DAYS IN COMBAT THE WHOLE WAR.

28:20.433 --> 28:24.034
IN IRAQ,
I DID 310 MY FIRST TOUR ALONE.

28:24.036 --> 28:26.870
I'VE DONE FOUR ROTATIONS.
THE BRASS WAS PLANNING A FIFTH.

28:26.872 --> 28:28.038
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

28:28.040 --> 28:30.007
I COULDN'T DO IT ANYMORE,
SO I WENT AWOL.

28:32.478 --> 28:35.979
I COULDN'T GO
TO MY OWN SON'S FUNERAL.

28:36.982 --> 28:40.918
I DIDN'T KILL TOM.

28:40.920 --> 28:43.287
I HOPE NOT.

28:43.289 --> 28:45.022
[ SIGHS ]

28:45.024 --> 28:50.094
FOR YOUR SAKE,
I HOPE NOT.

29:02.341 --> 29:04.775
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
I KNOW HE WAS YOUR SON.

29:08.914 --> 29:11.215
I'M SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

29:22.228 --> 29:25.362
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

29:25.364 --> 29:27.131
WHAT IS IT?

29:27.133 --> 29:28.866
[ SIGHS ]

29:28.868 --> 29:31.869
BEN,
WHAT'S WRONG?

29:31.871 --> 29:33.904
BEN,
WHAT IS IT?

29:33.906 --> 29:35.873
SCOTT DIDN'T DO IT.

29:35.875 --> 29:37.808
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

29:37.810 --> 29:38.909
HE DIDN'T KILL TOM.

29:38.911 --> 29:40.244
YES.
OF COURSE HE DID.

29:40.246 --> 29:41.945
THERE'S NO WAY.
HE HAD TO.

29:41.947 --> 29:43.464
CORNELL LET HIM GO.
WHY?

29:43.465 --> 29:44.982
WHY WOULD SHE LET HIM GO?
HE HAD AN ALIBI!

29:44.984 --> 29:46.216
THEN WHO DID THIS?
WHO WOULD DO THIS...

29:46.218 --> 29:47.384
I DON'T KNOW.
...TO MY LITTLE BOY?

29:47.386 --> 29:49.253
I HAVE TO KNOW!
I<i> NEED</i> TO KNOW!

29:49.255 --> 29:50.921
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

29:50.923 --> 29:54.992
CAN'T JUST LIVE NOT KNOWING
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY SON!

29:54.994 --> 29:56.260
WHAT IF
THEY NEVER FIND OUT?

29:56.262 --> 29:57.394
<i> I</i> WILL FIND OUT.

29:57.396 --> 30:00.531
I'LL FIND OUT,
AND THEY'RE GONNA PAY.

30:00.533 --> 30:02.900
DO YOU PROMISE ME?
YES.

30:02.902 --> 30:04.434
YES.

30:04.436 --> 30:07.271
I PROMISE.

30:07.273 --> 30:08.906
[ SHOWER RUNNING ]

30:08.908 --> 30:10.941
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
I'M HOME.

30:10.943 --> 30:12.843
[ SHOWER STOPS ]

30:12.845 --> 30:15.813
CAN YOU
HAND ME MY CLOTHES?

30:18.384 --> 30:22.986
THANKS.

31:02.328 --> 31:05.095
[ DOOR OPENS ]

31:10.569 --> 31:12.936
THOSE EARRINGS
ARE REALLY GREAT.

31:12.938 --> 31:16.073
THANKS.

31:16.075 --> 31:18.041
SO, WHERE ARE YOU
GOING TONIGHT?

31:18.043 --> 31:19.042
A BUSINESS DINNER.

31:19.044 --> 31:22.012
[ SIGHS ]

31:27.319 --> 31:30.320
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:31.957 --> 31:34.925
[ SCOFFS ]

31:34.927 --> 31:37.928
IS THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO ASK ME?

31:37.930 --> 31:40.664
YOU GONNA KEEP IT?

31:40.666 --> 31:42.099
KEEP WHAT?

31:42.101 --> 31:44.968
WELL, SINCE I KNOW
I'M NOT THE FATHER...

31:44.970 --> 31:47.070
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

31:47.072 --> 31:49.640
...MAYBE YOU WANT
TO KEEP THIS ONE.

31:49.642 --> 31:51.241
OKAY. UH...

31:51.243 --> 31:54.578
I SEE
HOW YOU GOT THERE.

31:54.580 --> 31:55.579
BUT YOU'RE WRONG.

31:55.581 --> 31:57.481
WHY DO YOU
HAVE THE TEST?

31:58.984 --> 32:03.053
I'VE NEVER
CHEATED ON YOU.

32:03.055 --> 32:05.055
THEN WHY
WAS IT IN THE BAG?

32:05.057 --> 32:07.090
LOOK, I KNOW
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

32:07.092 --> 32:09.159
AND I'M SORRY,
BUT I AM NOT PREPARED

32:09.161 --> 32:10.694
TO HAVE THIS CONVERSATION
RIGHT NOW.

32:10.696 --> 32:13.130
[ SCOFFS ]

32:13.131 --> 32:15.565
YOU SERIOUSLY THINK
YOU'RE GONNA WALK OUT NOW?!

32:15.567 --> 32:18.168
THIS IS
A LONGER CONVERSATION.

32:20.673 --> 32:25.008
I AM HAVING DINNER WITH THE
PARTNERS AND POTENTIAL CLIENTS.

32:25.010 --> 32:26.543
I DON'T CARE.

32:26.544 --> 32:28.077
YOU<i> SHOULD.</i>
WE NEED THE MONEY.

32:28.080 --> 32:29.313
SCREW THE MONEY.

32:29.314 --> 32:30.547
WE NEED
TO TALK ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW.

32:30.549 --> 32:34.952
WE WILL TALK ABOUT THIS
WHEN I GET HOME.

32:43.062 --> 32:49.199
[ HUMMING ]

32:49.201 --> 32:51.668
WHAT, AM I TOO LOUD?
WHAT IS IT?

32:51.670 --> 32:53.170
WHAT HAPPENED?

32:53.172 --> 32:54.304
[ SIGHS ]

32:54.306 --> 32:56.707
MY FLASHLIGHT
CAME BACK.

32:56.709 --> 32:59.076
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
WHAT?

32:59.078 --> 33:01.645
IT -- IT FELL OUT OF THE TRUCK
WHEN I OPENED IT.

33:01.647 --> 33:03.681
OKAY. [ SIGHS ]

33:03.682 --> 33:05.716
YOU DIDN'T MISS IT
THE FIRST TIME YOU LOOKED?

33:05.718 --> 33:07.150
SOMEBODY PUT IT THERE.

33:08.153 --> 33:09.720
OKAY.

33:09.722 --> 33:11.755
I THOUGHT
IT WAS SCOTT.

33:11.757 --> 33:13.941
UH-HUH.

33:13.942 --> 33:16.126
HE GOT INTO THE HOUSE SO EASY,
WHY NOT THE TRUCK, RIGHT?

33:16.128 --> 33:17.361
THAT MAKES SENSE.

33:17.363 --> 33:19.413
YEAH, IT DID,

33:19.414 --> 33:21.464
UNTIL I FOUND OUT
THAT SCOTT DIDN'T KILL TOM.

33:21.467 --> 33:23.767
WHAT ARE YOU TELLING ME?

33:23.769 --> 33:26.169
SO HE NEVER
HAD THE FLASHLIGHT.

33:29.308 --> 33:33.577
DO YOU EVEN KNOW IF THE
FLASHLIGHT IS THE MURDER WEAPON?

33:33.579 --> 33:35.145
IT IS.
UH-HUH.

33:36.648 --> 33:38.448
OKAY.

33:38.450 --> 33:40.083
YOU DIDN'T TOUCH IT,
DID YOU?

33:40.085 --> 33:41.418
I'M NOT STUPID.
I WIPED IT OFF.

33:41.420 --> 33:44.554
EINSTEIN,
THAT'S CALLED TAMPERING, OKAY?

33:44.556 --> 33:45.756
IT'S A FELONY.

33:45.758 --> 33:47.724
[ SIGHS ]
YEAH.

33:47.726 --> 33:49.259
THE LEAST
OF MY WORRIES.

33:49.261 --> 33:51.094
OH, MAN.

33:51.096 --> 33:52.596
THAT IS
REALLY STRANGE

33:52.597 --> 33:54.097
THAT THEY BROUGHT IT BACK
TO YOUR TRUCK, THOUGH.

33:54.099 --> 33:55.732
REALLY?
YOU THINK?

33:55.734 --> 33:58.435
I'M JUST SAYING

33:58.437 --> 34:01.805
THAT THEY COULD HAVE BROUGHT IT
TO THE COPS, YOU KNOW?

34:01.807 --> 34:04.508
THAT'S WHAT NORMAL PEOPLE
WOULD DO.

34:06.045 --> 34:07.077
WHAT?

34:07.079 --> 34:09.513
GOT TO GET RID OF IT.
HOW?

34:09.515 --> 34:11.615
SOMEONE IS TRYING
TO SET ME UP.

34:11.617 --> 34:13.283
IF I LEAVE HERE
TO GET RID OF IT,

34:13.285 --> 34:15.218
THEY'RE WATCHING ME,
CORNELL GETS A TIP,

34:15.220 --> 34:17.220
I GET PULLED OVER
WITH THE MURDER WEAPON.

34:17.222 --> 34:18.422
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL DO IT.

34:18.424 --> 34:20.190
I'LL GET RID OF IT.
I-I-I'LL DO IT.

34:20.192 --> 34:21.625
NO WAY.

34:21.626 --> 34:23.059
I-I-I'D NEVER ASK YOU
TO DO THAT.

34:23.062 --> 34:24.728
ANYWAY,
IT'S IN A SAFE PLACE.

34:24.730 --> 34:25.796
YOU SURE?

34:29.068 --> 34:30.500
OKAY.

34:30.502 --> 34:33.603
IN THAT CASE, CAN WE WATCH
THE PANTHERS GAME IN THE HOUSE?

34:33.605 --> 34:35.839
BECAUSE CHRISTY WENT OUT TO
HER FANCY DINNER MEETING, RIGHT?

34:35.841 --> 34:38.208
HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHERE CHRISTY WENT?

34:38.210 --> 34:40.510
[ LAUGHS NERVOUSLY ]
OKAY, HERE'S THE THING.

34:40.512 --> 34:42.079
IF YOUR BATHROOM WINDOW
IS OPEN,

34:42.081 --> 34:43.213
THEN I CAN HEAR
EVERY SINGLE --

34:43.215 --> 34:45.449
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME THAT SOONER?

34:45.451 --> 34:46.650
UH...

34:46.651 --> 34:47.850
ALL RIGHT, WHATEVER.
WHAT DID YOU HEAR?

34:47.853 --> 34:51.455
I'M NOT ONE
TO OFFER UP UNSOLICITED ADVICE,

34:51.457 --> 34:53.374
BUT SINCE YOU ASKED,

34:53.375 --> 34:55.292
I DO NOT THINK
THAT CHRISTY IS CHEATING ON YOU.

34:55.294 --> 34:57.160
THANKS.
OKAY, I'M JUST SAYING.

34:57.162 --> 34:59.362
I DON'T THINK
IT'S HER TEST, BROTHER.

34:59.364 --> 35:00.564
THEN WHOSE IS IT?

35:01.867 --> 35:05.469
OKAY, SHERLOCK,
PROCESS OF ELIMINATION.

35:05.471 --> 35:08.472
IT'S NOT MINE, IT'S NOT YOURS,
IT'S NOT ABBY'S...

35:08.474 --> 35:10.807
IT AIN'T CHRISTY'S...

35:10.809 --> 35:12.759
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
OKAY.

35:12.760 --> 35:14.710
ALL RIGHT. BREATHE IT OUT.
BREATHE IT OUT, BROTHER.

35:15.714 --> 35:17.380
NATALIE!

35:17.382 --> 35:19.416
SHE'S NOT HERE.

35:19.418 --> 35:21.251
WHERE IS SHE?

35:21.253 --> 35:23.320
YOU TOLD ME
TO RESPECT HER PRIVACY.

35:23.322 --> 35:25.122
THIS IS DIFFERENT.

35:25.124 --> 35:27.224
I WON'T GET MAD
AT YOU.

35:28.727 --> 35:30.794
HONEY, THIS IS ABOUT
YOUR SISTER'S SAFETY.

35:30.796 --> 35:31.862
I WILL NOT GET MAD.

35:31.864 --> 35:34.498
SHE WENT
TO COOPER'S PARTY.

35:35.734 --> 35:36.800
[ STOMPS FOOT ]

35:36.801 --> 35:37.867
YOU SAID
YOU WOULDN'T GET MAD.

35:37.870 --> 35:39.836
I SAID THAT I WOULDN'T GET MAD
AT<i> YOU.</i>

35:39.838 --> 35:41.705
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE COOPER LIVES?

35:41.707 --> 35:43.707
SWEETHEART,
I PROMISE I WON'T BE MAD.

35:43.709 --> 35:46.309
I'M 85% SURE
HE TOTALLY MEANS IT.

35:50.916 --> 35:53.884
IS THAT
NATALIE'S LAPTOP?

35:53.886 --> 35:56.219
YOU PROMISED.

36:03.462 --> 36:04.728
IT'S LIKE THE NSA.

36:08.300 --> 36:09.933
Dave:
HEY, HEY, HEY.

36:09.935 --> 36:11.385
OKAY.

36:11.386 --> 36:12.836
MAYBE YOU WANT
TO COUNT TO 10 FIRST.

36:12.838 --> 36:16.673
WAIT WITH ABBY.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.708
[ INDISTINCT TALKING, LAUGHTER ]

36:18.710 --> 36:20.810
[ LOUD DANCE MUSIC PLAYING ]

36:29.755 --> 36:31.188
HEY!

36:39.932 --> 36:41.231
DAMN!

36:43.235 --> 36:45.535
[ ALL CHEER ]

36:48.640 --> 36:50.207
NATALIE!

36:51.810 --> 36:53.343
DAD?

36:53.345 --> 36:54.844
LET'S GO.
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

36:54.846 --> 36:56.780
NO, GET OUT --
I'M TAKING
MY DAUGHTER HOME.

36:56.782 --> 36:58.381
I HATE YOU.
I'LL GET USED TO IT.

36:58.383 --> 37:00.217
SHE DOESN'T WANT TO GO.
GET OUT OF MY FACE.

37:00.219 --> 37:01.418
[ CROWD MURMURS ]

37:02.354 --> 37:03.787
Natalie: NO!

37:03.789 --> 37:05.922
YOU COME NEAR MY DAUGHTER AGAIN,
AND I WILL KILL YOU.

37:06.992 --> 37:08.792
GO OUTSIDE
AND GET IN THE TRUCK.

37:08.794 --> 37:09.926
I AM NOT
GOING ANYWHERE WITH YOU.

37:09.928 --> 37:11.895
YOU GO OUTSIDE
RIGHT NOW!

37:11.897 --> 37:13.897
OR WHAT?
ARE YOU GONNA KILL ME, TOO?

37:13.899 --> 37:14.898
Dave:
OH, MAN.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.933
NAT-- NATALIE,
COME HERE.

37:16.935 --> 37:18.902
THAT'S ENOUGH.
LITTLE DRUNK.

37:18.904 --> 37:21.671
[ CHUCKLES ]
SHE'S JUST A LITTLE DRUNK.

37:26.979 --> 37:30.313
THERE'S NO WAY
I'M GOING ANYWHERE WITH HIM.

37:30.315 --> 37:31.932
NATALIE...

37:31.933 --> 37:33.550
I AM<i> NOT</i> GETTING
IN THAT TRUCK WITH YOU.

37:34.786 --> 37:36.853
FINE.
DAVE'LL TAKE YOU.

37:36.855 --> 37:39.022
WHAT,
ARE YOU GONNA WALK?

37:39.024 --> 37:40.790
DAD.

37:40.792 --> 37:41.992
DADDY.

37:41.994 --> 37:45.729
I WANT
TO GO WITH YOU.

37:47.599 --> 37:49.399
DAD?

37:49.401 --> 37:50.400
YEAH?

37:50.402 --> 37:53.770
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH NATALIE?

37:53.772 --> 37:56.273
I DON'T KNOW.

37:56.275 --> 38:00.810
I JUST WANT THINGS TO GO BACK
TO THE WAY THEY USED TO BE.

38:00.812 --> 38:02.946
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

38:02.948 --> 38:05.448
SO DO I, MONKEY.

38:05.450 --> 38:06.883
SO DO I.

38:06.885 --> 38:09.386
ALL RIGHT.
YEAH.

38:23.635 --> 38:26.903
Ben: I KNOW
IT WAS NATALIE'S.

38:26.905 --> 38:29.472
I WANTED
TO TELL YOU.

38:29.474 --> 38:30.874
YOU SHOULD'VE.

38:30.876 --> 38:35.545
I NEVER MEANT
FOR YOU TO FIND OUT THIS WAY.

38:35.547 --> 38:38.682
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH MY KIDS.

38:38.684 --> 38:42.319
YOU'RE RIGHT.

38:42.321 --> 38:44.321
I'M SORRY.
[ SIGHS ]

38:44.323 --> 38:48.558
LOOK, SHE ONLY TOLD ME BECAUSE
I PROMISED I WOULDN'T TELL YOU.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.227
OUR KIDS
ARE SO LUCKY

38:50.228 --> 38:51.895
TO HAVE TWO PARENTS
WHO CARE SO MUCH ABOUT THEM,

38:51.897 --> 38:54.331
PARENTS WHO<i> WANT</i> TO KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON IN THEIR LIVES

38:54.333 --> 38:56.183
SO THEY CAN ACT

38:56.184 --> 38:58.034
BEFORE SOMETHING COMES ALONG
THAT THEY CAN'T FIX.

38:59.905 --> 39:02.906
BEN...

39:02.908 --> 39:04.874
THERE WAS NOTHING
YOU COULD DO.

39:04.876 --> 39:07.877
I DIDN'T PROTECT HIM.

39:07.879 --> 39:09.846
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS YOUR JOB.

39:12.117 --> 39:15.618
I HATE
WHAT HAPPENED TO TOM.

39:15.620 --> 39:17.887
I HATE
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO US.

39:17.889 --> 39:20.957
I HATE WHAT IT'S GONNA DO
TO OUR GIRLS.

39:20.959 --> 39:25.729
WELL, THERE'S NOT ANYTHING WE
CAN DO TO CHANGE THAT RIGHT NOW.

39:29.034 --> 39:33.970
I THINK YOU SHOULD START
SLEEPING IN OUR BEDROOM AGAIN.

39:33.972 --> 39:37.006
ABBY'S ASKING QUESTIONS.

39:37.008 --> 39:40.043
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

39:44.750 --> 39:46.066
IT'S OKAY.

39:46.067 --> 39:47.383
I JUST NEED TO SPEAK
WITH MR. CRAWFORD.

39:47.386 --> 39:48.985
I THINK
I'LL STAY.

39:50.689 --> 39:53.623
[<i> LOUD DANCE MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

39:53.625 --> 39:56.025
Natalie:<i> NO!</i>

39:56.027 --> 39:59.162
Ben:<i> YOU COME NEAR MY DAUGHTER</i>
<i>AGAIN, AND I WILL KILL YOU.</i>

39:59.164 --> 40:01.498
<i> GO OUTSIDE</i>
<i>AND GET IN THE TRUCK.</i>

40:01.500 --> 40:03.433
I'M GUESSING
YOU DIDN'T NOTICE

40:03.435 --> 40:05.635
THE 50 TEENAGERS
FILMING YOU?

40:05.637 --> 40:07.437
IT'S UNFORTUNATE
YOU PICKED THAT MOMENT

40:07.439 --> 40:09.939
TO ASSAULT AND THREATEN TO KILL
YOUR DAUGHTER'S BOYFRIEND.

40:09.941 --> 40:13.443
I NEED A STATEMENT
FROM MR. LINDSEY.

40:13.445 --> 40:15.912
I'LL GET DAVE
FOR YOU.

40:18.817 --> 40:20.950
THANK YOU.
MM.

40:20.952 --> 40:22.786
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

40:22.788 --> 40:25.021
[ Yawning ]
WHAT UP, G?

40:25.023 --> 40:27.857
HEY, MAN, UH,
CORNELL'S BACK.

40:27.859 --> 40:30.693
THERE WAS A VIDEO
POSTED ON YouTube.

40:30.695 --> 40:32.896
YOU TELLING ME SOME DOUCHE-LING
CAUGHT YOU ON HIS CELLIE?

40:32.898 --> 40:35.098
WHY THE HELL
DOES THAT ALWAYS HAPPEN?

40:35.100 --> 40:36.900
SHE WANTS
YOUR STATEMENT.

40:36.902 --> 40:38.935
HEY, I DIDN'T
SEE NOTHING, MAN.

40:38.937 --> 40:40.937
AS MUCH AS I MIGHT NEED YOU
TO LIE FOR ME AT A LATER DATE,

40:40.939 --> 40:42.605
IT'S PROBABLY BETTER
YOU TELL THE TRUTH.

40:42.607 --> 40:44.007
[ SIGHS ]

40:45.977 --> 40:47.577
COME ON.

40:47.579 --> 40:48.945
OW.

40:48.947 --> 40:50.814
WHAT? WHAT?

40:50.816 --> 40:52.782
HEY, MAN.
HEY, HEY.

40:52.784 --> 40:53.917
OH, WHOA.

40:53.919 --> 40:55.985
I-I-IT'S NOT
WHAT YOU THINK, ALL RIGHT?

40:55.987 --> 40:57.120
LISTEN -- LISTEN,
SHE WAS DRUNK, BROTHER.

40:57.122 --> 40:58.955
I WANT YOU
OUT OF MY HOUSE NOW!!

40:58.957 --> 41:00.623
YOU DON'T MEAN IT. COME ON.
NOW!!

41:00.625 --> 41:01.825
YOU -- HEY!
I DON'T?

41:01.827 --> 41:02.959
I DON'T NEED --
LISTEN TO ME!

41:02.961 --> 41:04.628
YOU BETTER GO,
MAN.

41:04.629 --> 41:06.296
I SWEAR TO GOD, MAN.
COME ON. COME ON, COME ON.

41:06.297 --> 41:07.964
YOU KNOW THAT I WOULD
NEVER, NEVER DO ANYTHING
LIKE THAT. PLEASE. PLEASE.

41:07.966 --> 41:08.898
GET OUT
OF MY HOUSE.

41:08.900 --> 41:10.066
BRO.
BRO, CALM DOWN.

41:10.068 --> 41:11.968
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!
I SWEAR TO YOU!

41:11.970 --> 41:13.303
I SWEAR TO YOU.

41:13.304 --> 41:14.637
I SWEAR TO YOU,
I DIDN'T DO NOTHING, OKAY?

41:14.639 --> 41:15.972
I-I'M BEGGING YOU,
PLEASE.

41:15.974 --> 41:17.807
YOU'RE MAKING
A REALLY BIG MISTAKE HERE.

41:17.809 --> 41:20.977
BIGGEST MISTAKE I EVER MADE
WAS HAVING YOU FOR A FRIEND!

41:20.979 --> 41:24.013
YOU NEED A RIDE,
MR. LINDSEY?

41:24.015 --> 41:25.014
SURE.

41:25.016 --> 41:26.950
GO!

41:26.952 --> 41:29.586
[ SIGHS ]

41:29.588 --> 41:31.488
YEAH.

41:31.490 --> 41:36.793
YEAH,
I GUESS I DO.

41:36.795 --> 41:39.929
Cornell: I'M GONNA NEED
TO GET SOMETHING TO EAT.

41:39.931 --> 41:41.931
YOU MIND
IF WE STOP ON THE WAY?

41:41.933 --> 41:44.701
YEAH,
I COULD EAT.

41:44.703 --> 41:45.902
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
